Test Case 1: Mode Switch When Device Is Connected

Test Case ID: TC-01
Title: Verify listening mode can be changed when device is connected


Preconditions:
Device is paired and in an active Bluetooth connection state with the app
Device is in idle state


Test Steps:
1.Open the app.
2.Ensure the device is connected.
3.Set the listening mode as @Listening Mods.
4.Confirm the selection.
5.Verify the mode is applied successfully on both app and device.
6.Repeat steps 3–5 for all @Listening Mods.


Mode Table
| @Listening Mods    |
| ------------------ |
| Noise Cancellation |
| Transparency Mode  |



Expected Result:
Listening mode is successfully updated on the device.
App UI reflects the newly selected mode.
Device sends acknowledgment confirming mode change.

